Here's how to handle each scenario in MSTest:

## 1. Windows-Only Tests

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
// Or with a simple condition:
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("WindowsOnly")]
public void RegistryTest()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows");
    // ... registry code
}
```

## 2. Skip in CI (requires local GPU)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void GpuTest()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") == "true")
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI - requires local GPU");
    // ... GPU test
}
```

Filter in CI with: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"`

## 3. Flaky External API — Retry with `[DataRow]` or custom attribute

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Timeout(10000)]
public void WeatherApiTest()
{
    int maxRetries = 3;
    Exception? last = null;

    for (int i = 0; i < maxRetries; i++)
    {
        try
        {
            var result = CallWeatherApi();
            Assert.IsNotNull(result);
            return; // success
        }
        catch (HttpRequestException ex)
        {
            last = ex;
            Thread.Sleep(1000 * (i + 1)); // backoff
        }
    }
    Assert.Fail($"Flaky API failed after {maxRetries} retries: {last?.Message}");
}
```

## 4. Cleanup Even on Failure — Use `[TestCleanup]` or `try/finally`

```csharp
[TestClass]
public class TempFileTests
{
    private string? _tempFile;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestCleanup]
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        // Runs even if the test fails
        if (_tempFile != null && File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void ProcessTempFile()
    {
        File.WriteAllText(_tempFile!, "test data");
        // ... test logic that might fail
        Assert.IsTrue(File.Exists(_tempFile));
    }
}
```

**Key takeaways:**
| Scenario | Pattern |
|----------|---------|
| OS-specific | `Assert.Inconclusive()` guard or filter by category |
| Skip in CI | Environment variable check + `--filter` |
| Flaky APIs | Retry loop with backoff + `[Timeout]` |
| Cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` (always runs, even on failure) |
